						<summary>

						<p>Pallava, Nandivarman II, 22nd year = A.D. 753.</p>						

						<p>The characters of the inscription belong to the eleventh century. In fact it is stated at the end that this is a copy of an earlier stone inscription. A woman called Chandippeliyār purchased land from the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Tiribuvanamādēvi-chaturvēdimaṅgalam as <hi rend="italic">ūrkīḻ-iṟaiyili</hi> and endowed it for offerings and a lamp, to the temple of Tiruvaigāvuḍaiya-Mahādēva.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XII, No. 58).</p>						

						</summary>
